[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Raises the max quality of grave items and decorations from the vanilla cap to 30, so high-tier builds aren't penalised by arbitrary limits.[/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][b]Max quality lifted to 30[/b] — grave stones, fences, covers, and decorations can all now count their full quality toward the grave score instead of being clipped at vanilla's lower cap.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Body skull cap bypass[/b] — vanilla caps the grave quality at the body's white-skull count. That cap is also lifted so your high-quality builds count fully even on lower-skull bodies.[/size]
[*][size=3]No unlock required — applies the moment the mod loads. Works on existing graves the next time the game recalculates their quality (on load, on placement, on zone refresh).[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/62]Where's Ma' Storage[/url] — shared inventory across workstations. Carrying around grave-item sets becomes much less painful.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/86]Decomp Delight[/url] — element tags on every researched item's tooltip for efficient alchemy.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/57]Queue Everything[/url] — queue morgue-table crafts. Per-workbench auto-craft supports the morgue, packing, and autopsy tables.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/60]I Build Where I Want[/url] — place grave structures anywhere, not just in pre-defined plots.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79][size=3]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack at Graveyard Keeper Nexus - Mods and community (nexusmods.com)[/size][/url]
[/list]
[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:

[code]...&#92;steamapps&#92;common&#92;Graveyard Keeper&#92;BepInEx[/code][/size]

